============================================================================
User visible changes for handshake-node
  A Handshake full node implementation written in Go
============================================================================

Changes in 0.2.0-rc1 (release candidate)
  - Consensus and hsd compatibility:
    - Enforce hsd claim and airdrop hardening, sequence locks, bounded future
      covenants, proof admission, mining policy, and coinbase limits.
      (#52, #53, #55, #61, #62)
    - Use Handshake-native hash text order and canonical mainnet checkpoints.
      (#65, #66)
    - Align output policy, block locator limits, bloom filtering, and partial
      Merkle proof construction with hsd. (#67, #76, #82, #83)
  - Proof relay, mempool, and mining:
    - Add raw hsd claim and airdrop proof conversion, peer relay, and
      sendrawclaim/sendrawairdrop RPC submission. (#56)
    - Serve name proofs for committed Urkel roots and rate-limit inbound proof
      requests. (#63, #64)
    - Remove a gettxout mempool race. (#68)
  - RPC and operator features:
    - Add hsd-compatible RPCs for resource decoding, block lookup, mempool graph
      inspection, and network information. (#54)
    - Add a resumable hsd v8 mainnet parity runner and documented readiness
      gates. (#59)
  - Network and security hardening:
    - Bound RPC bodies, proof payloads, transaction and witness allocations,
      and security-sensitive integer conversions. (#57, #60, #61, #72)
    - Reject invalid headers and trailing structured payloads while retaining
      compatibility with future Handshake message types. (#69, #73, #74)
    - Require Go 1.26.5 and add govulncheck and multi-architecture container
      vulnerability gates. (#77)
  - Testing and maintenance:
    - Exercise pinned hsd transports, relay, reorganization, restart,
      persistence, malformed-peer, and recovery behavior. (#75, #78, #79)
    - Restore Handshake-native tokenizer, mempool-accept, database, and chain
      fixture coverage. (#70, #71, #80, #81)
    - Remove remaining Bitcoin and wallet remnants. (#58)
  - Migration notes:
    - RPC, configuration, checkpoint, and outpoint hash strings now use hsd's
      native Handshake byte order. (#65)
    - The default regtest RPC port is now 14037, hnsctl no longer provides
      wallet defaults, and source builds require Go 1.26.5 or newer. (#58, #77)
  - Contributors (alphabetical order):
    - Chris Gianelloni

Changes in 0.1.1-rc1 (release candidate)
  - Consensus and validation hardening:
    - Enforce Handshake claim and airdrop cutoff heights. (#51)
  - Release metadata note:
    - The tag was cut before its version metadata was updated, so its binaries
      identify themselves as 0.1.0-rc1. Later fixes are included above in the
      actual v0.1.1-rc1-to-v0.2.0-rc1 release range.

Changes in 0.1.0-rc1 (release candidate)
  - Handshake protocol and consensus changes:
    - Implement Handshake mainnet and regtest chain parameters, block headers,
      proof-of-work, transactions, covenants, and name state transitions.
    - Validate Blake2b/SHA3 proof-of-work, covenant state, name roots, witness
      roots, and coinbase airdrop proofs.
    - Maintain Urkel-backed name state with rollback support and hsd-compatible
      name proof generation.
  - Peer-to-peer and sync changes:
    - Implement Handshake packet framing, inventory, name proof messages, and
      Brontide transport with plaintext compatibility during migration.
    - Preserve Brontide static keys through address relay and outbound dialing.
    - Harden initial block download and malformed peer handling.
  - Mempool and mining changes:
    - Validate name covenants during mempool admission and template selection.
    - Implement Handshake block-template fields and coinbase proof sourcing.
    - Add an opt-in Handshake Stratum v1 server for local mining integration.
  - RPC, CLI, and wallet integration changes:
    - Add Handshake name RPCs, notifications, client helpers, and unsigned
      covenant construction for external wallets.
    - Keep keys, signing, coin selection, and wallet state outside the node.
    - Harden RPC authentication, listeners, allowlists, and configuration.
  - Release and operator changes:
    - Update module paths, binaries, documentation, containers, CI, and release
      publishing for handshake-node.
    - Require Go 1.25 or newer for source builds.
